race.comment: AUTHORATIVE (1) is a long-standing maiden, but he's been running strong figures in stronger events than this recently. He looks well placed back to Country grade with Gaerth replacing the apprentice hoop. Should land in a handy spot and give himself every chance. PROVE ME WRONG (8) ran on well from a long way back first-up over 1100m at Toodyay and looks well placed up in distance today. Faithfull hopping on board is a positive sign and she looks a genuine contender out to a more suitable distance for her. FLY AWAY FLIRT (3) was strong from the front first-up but just felt the pinch late, beaten 2.7L at Toodyay 11 days ago. Up in trip now looks to suit and she performed strongly in a very similar race to this when second-up last campaign. Can feature in the finish. IFFUBLUSH (9) was very good when right back in trip last start and if she can hold that form today, she'll go close. LATORIO (5) can strike third-up and off an inside barrier.
